Step By Step Instructions
=========================
1.) Open up the file Makefile in your favorite editor. (vim)
2.) Edit the Local Configuration section to fit your needs (save it)
3.) $ make
4.) $ su
      password:
5.) $ make install
6.) If you don't want to manually start the daemon each time, just
    add it to your rc.local file. (Info on this can be found in the README)
7.) You Are Done Have Fun! (Next time you re-boot it will start the daemon)
NOTE: If you dont wan't to reboot you can just execute the rc.local script
by doing
	(Linux)
	$ source /etc/rc.d/rc.local
	(OpenBSD)
	$ source /etc/rc.local

END OF FILE
